Hope'. It failed. Not because it couldn't have worked but because the project wasn't started until too late. We should have built nuclear rockets 50 years ago. <br>I wonder if we will end up talking about options for 15 years and taking decisive action too late. Nothing would surprise me. We have known of the serious threat from asteroids for decades and nothing but talk has ever come of it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/uarkuunaves.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ArkuunAves</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Space Tourist</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(7/24/02 9:40:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=116.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/radman.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Can even a positive asteroid threat get things moving?</span><hr size=1> new reports are that scientists have determined that we roughly have no f-ing clue how close it's gonna come to us, but that's it's about one in a couple billion chances it'll hit, on a rough scale.<br><br>heh, i just read something about this actually,i forget wher...but yeah, the hype around it is mainly bogus. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm12.showNextMessage?topicID=116.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=116.topic&index=1><img src=http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/addreply3.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1